profile_positions.description:
In this position my responsibilities and tasks are twofold. On the one hand I am leading Oxfam Novib's "Responsible Investments in Conflict and Fragile Areas" program, on the other hand I am responsible for our advocacy towards the Dutch government and public in regards to the Occupied Palestinian Territories/Israel. Besides, I am a member of the Workers Council and I co-founded Young Oxfam Novib (YON).

Responsibilities as a policy advisor "responsible investments in fragile and conflict areas":
● Lead "private sector in conflict" program of Oxfam Novib, ensure linkages between country project(s) and regional and global influencing;
● Conduct research on the conflict sensitivity of Dutch Private Sector Development Policies and Instruments;
● Engage with the Dutch government concerning the conflict sensitivity of the Dutch Private Sector Development Policies, organize meetings to connect relevant policy makers and stimulate discussion about this topic;
● Support country projects as focal point on content, quality implementation, learning, linking to regional and global influencing;
● Develop and draft (multi-country) proposals to raise new funds;
● Maintain relationships with partners working on similar issues, search for new opportunities and participate in multi-stakeholder platforms.

Responsibilities as policy advisor OPT/I:
● Engage with the Dutch government and MPs regarding the political and economical situation in OPT/I, particularly concerning the blockade of Gaza, settlements (implementation UN-resolution 2334) and civic space/ human rights defenders;
● Organize lobby tours and missions of Palestinian and Israeli partner organizations and UN representatives (OCHA);
● Analyze political and legislative developments in the Netherlands in regards to OPT/I.

As (interim) project manager for Oxfam in Myanmar I am managing the project “Towards Conflict Sensitive and Inclusive Investments in Myanmar”, which is a joint project together with our national partner MATA. The project seeks to promote enhanced transparency, consultation, participation and benefit sharing around investments, and understanding of the impact of investment on conflict affected communities, through a combination of capacity building of our partner, influencing private sector and government actors to engage with key stakeholders, influencing the government and key stakeholders.

Tasks and responsibilities:
 ● Manage the project with local partner: monitor and ensure project spending according to agreed budget, maintain oversight of the project, write annual report;
● Work closely with local partner to ensure project delivery: provide technical and practical support in order to implement activities such as a private sector engagement training and conflict assessments, maintaining contact with consultants;
● Develop project proposal next phase: organize reflection sessions with partner, develop new ToC, write new project proposal and agree on new budget;
● Support the development of the Responsible Investments Toolkit;
● Apply the MEAL framework and collect data.

Tasks and responsibilities:
● Evaluate the annual budget of the newly elected government;
● Formulate questions and reaction to the proposed budget;
● Write letters to the government to inform MPs about humanitarian crises such as in Myanmar/ Bangladesh;
● Track policy discussions and developments emanating from the Dutch Ministry of Foreign Affairs and parliament on Oxfam Novib’s priority issues;
● Pro-actively participate and organize meetings with relevant ambassadors, MPs and policy makers.

As a Policy Advisor at Oxfam Nobib I am concerned with with the societal and environmental impact of companies operating in different value chains, among which agriculture and the financial sector. I support country offices in the development of a strategy to influence the private sector to improve their 'Responsible Business Conduct', collect and analyse practical experiences of Oxfam on this particular subject and develop international programs and proposals on Business and Human Rights.

Tasks:
● Developing a 'Private Sector Capacity Building Support Package' for country offices which will be used for workshops on private sector influencing. Analyzing Oxfam's strategies and the concept 'Responsible Business Conduct', of which a specific part is focussed on agribusiness in particular, and developing a plan for Oxfam country offices and affiliates to co-create on Private Sector influencing programs;
● Delivering a workshop to 3 country offices in Africa on Private Sector influencing;
● Anayzing the practical experiences in addressing key challenges in Responsible Business Conduct, both within Oxfam as well as outside, (such as 'due diligence', 'Free, Prior and Informed Consent', gender responsiveness, certification schemes etc.) and in this way providing concrete tools and approaches to reinforce Oxfam Strategic Partnership influencing messages and strategies;
● Developing (international) programs and fundraising proposals on Business and Human Rights

As a Policy Officer at Oxfam Novib I am concerned with the impact of companies in different commodities and value chains, among which agriculture and the financial sector. I develop a new international program that enables Oxfam to hold businesses accountable for their human rights policies and practices. In addition, I am involved with the Dutch CSR 'Sector Covenants' of the insurance sector. On behalf of Oxfam I lobby and advocate for sustainable investments by insurance companies.

Tasks:
● Developing a Theory of Change (TOC), an international program on the 'UN Guiding Principles on Business and Human Rights' (UNGPs) and a donor strategy;
● Writing and developing a concept note (application) for a EU fund (EIDHR) about the palm-oil value chain, in cooperation with Oxfam in Indonesia and Nigeria and local partners;
● Negotiate and lobby with the insurance industry in order to ensure sustainable and just investments;
● Analysing Oxfams' business and human rights projects, creating a track record, gathering best practices and lessons learnt;
● Delivering input for a Business and Human Rights Guidance (see link below);
● Participating in a multi-stakeholder project between companies, UN Global Compact and Oxfam;
● Maintaining contacts with country offices;
● Integrating the Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) with Human Rights (UNGPs) in research;
● I also developed a stakeholder power analyses, drafted a Terms of Reference (TOR) for evaluation and procurements, developed a multi-stakeholder partnership policy on the Strategic Partnerships, wrote a position paper and followed a security training.

Other competencies:
● Analytical;
● Strong (English) writing skills;
● Pro-active and entrepreneurial;
● Able to understand new subjects and matters quickly.

This traineeship is part of the Masters Degree 'Advanced Master for International Development' (AMID) in Nijmegen.

Horizons is a global youth movement that strives for just societies based on equality and fostered by intercultural understanding.
Horizons promotes intercultural dialogue between youth, fosters cooperation between the East and the West, creates awareness about injustice and inequality, empowers youth to promote mutual respect and envisions being the voice of youth who speak out against radicalism and intolerance and calls upon politicians to implement and pursue just policies worldwide.

